<p>For a long time I'm searching for a query that could turn my game result table in a Pivot/crosstab.</p>  <p>This is the basic table:</p>  <pre><code>home | away | round |  T1   | T1   |     0 |  T2   | T1   |     4 |  T3   | T1   |     5 |  T4   | T1   |     6 |  T1   | T2   |     1 |  T2   | T2   |     0 |  T3   | T2   |     5 |  T4   | T2   |     2 |  T1   | T3   |     2 |  T2   | T3   |     6 |  T3   | T3   |     0 |  T4   | T3   |     4 |  T1   | T4   |     5 |  T2   | T4   |     3 |  T3   | T4   |     1 |  T4   | T4   |     0 |  </code></pre>  <p>and this is what I really would like to get.</p>  <pre><code>   |T1 |T2 |T3 |T4| T1 | 0 | 1 | 2 |5 | T2 | 4 | 0 | 6 |3 | T3 | 5 | 5 | 0 |1 | T4 | 6 | 2 | 4 |0 | </code></pre>